=head1 DESCRIPTION

Provides the configuration information to include certain types of
GitHub content. You can configure to index repository files only, or
also include issues and pull requests, comments, and comment
attachments.

=head1 ATTRIBUTES


=head2 CrawlIssue => Bool

C<TRUE> to index all issues within a repository.


=head2 CrawlIssueComment => Bool

C<TRUE> to index all comments on issues.


=head2 CrawlIssueCommentAttachment => Bool

C<TRUE> to include all comment attachments for issues.


=head2 CrawlPullRequest => Bool

C<TRUE> to index all pull requests within a repository.


=head2 CrawlPullRequestComment => Bool

C<TRUE> to index all comments on pull requests.


=head2 CrawlPullRequestCommentAttachment => Bool

C<TRUE> to include all comment attachments for pull requests.


=head2 CrawlRepositoryDocuments => Bool

C<TRUE> to index all files with a repository.



